en_345651_0	The existing windy condition is expected to strengthen over the country and in the sea areas around the island in next few days, from the 06th of this month.
en_345651_1	According to the Department of Meteorology, the prevailing showers and cloudy conditions in the South-western part will continue further.
en_345651_2	Showers or thundershowers will occur at times in Western, Southern, Sabaragamuwa, Central and North-Western provinces and a few places in Ampara and Badulla districts after 2.00p.m.
en_345651_3	Fairly heavy falls of above 75 mm can be expected at some places, particularly in Sabaragamuwa and Central provinces.
en_345651_4	Light showers may occur at few places in Anuradhapura district.
en_345651_5	Fairly strong gusty winds up to 50 kmph can be expected over Southern province and Monaragala, Matale, Nuwara-Eliya and Polonnaruwa districts.
